@{b}@{u}Preface@{uu}@{ub}

@{b}Spitfire@{ub} is offered to you under the concept of @{i}Shareware@{ui}. You may use @{b}Spitfire@{ub} for an evaluation period of up to 30 days without paying any fee. If you are going to use @{i}Spitfire@{ui} after the evaluation period, you have to register.

See @{"License" link License} and @{"Shareware" link Registration} for more information.
@endnode

@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Features"
@prev "Preface"
@{b}What is Spitfire?@{ub}

In a nutshell, Spitfire is a Palm Desktop for the AmigaOS. It provides a connection to 3Com's Palm Pilot Personal, Palm Pilot Professional, Palm III, Palm IIIx, Palm V, or compatible, and allows a user to HotSync these devcies with their Amiga.

@endnode

@node "Features" "Features"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Introduction"

@{b}@{u}Features@{uu}@{ub}

  Currently, Spitfire supports the following main features:

    · Full backup and restoring of Palm databases and files.
    · Multiple user support.
    · Install of files (prc, pdb) with or without a complete HotSync.
    · Changing of user name ids.
    · Add/Delete/Edit Memos, with synchronization!
    · Add/Delete/Edit Addresses, with synchronization!
    · Add/Delete/Edit To Do items, with synchronization!
    · Viewing of Datebook events.
    · Import/Export of Memos in ASCII format.
    · Import/Export of Addresses in CSV format.
    · Import/Export of Address with Contact Manager.
    · Easy configurability with support of any serial device.
    · Localization

@endnode

@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@next "License"
@prev "Features"

@{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

  · Amiga with 020/2Mb or better
  · An available serial port.
  · Palm Pilot with it's cradle plugged into a serial port.
  · AmigaOS 3.0 or greater.
  · MUI 3.8 or greater.
    - third-party MCC classes:
      · InfoText
      · TextInput
      · NList
      · MonthNavigator
  · palmlink.library 1.0 or greater
  · date.library

 The install script will properly install all necessary parts from the Spitfire archive.

@endnode

