@node Conduits "Conduits"

@{b}@{u}The Conduits@{uu}@{ub}

  Spitfire currently supports the following conduits:
    1) @{"Install" link Install}
    2) @{"System " link System}
    3) @{"Memo   " link Memo}
    4) @{"Address" link Address}
    5) @{"To Do  " link ToDo}
    6) @{"Date   " link Date}
@endnode

@node Install "Install"
@{b}@{u}Install@{uu}@{ub}

  This conduits has no other interface other than what appears when double-clicking on its entry in the conduit action listview.  In this GUI, you can delete or add new applications to be installed at HotSync.
@endnode

@node System "System"
@{b}@{u}System@{uu}@{ub}

  This conduit has no interface and has the function of backup/restoring files that are not managed by the other conduits.
@endnode

@node Memo "Memo"
@{b}@{u}Memo@{uu}@{ub}

  The Memo allows the viewing, editing, deleting, and adding of items.  Selecting an item allows its contents to be viewed in the right-hand side area.  Double-clicking of items opens up an edit window for that item.

  It is also possible to import and export ascii files from the Memo pad.
  · To export, just select all the required files, and select Export form the pull-down menus.  In the request, type in the base name for the memos to be saved.  Each memo will be saved as an Ascii text file.
  · To import ascii files, select Import from the pull-down menus, and select all required files for importing from the file requester.  Each selected file will be imported as a seperate memo item.
@endnode

@node Address "Address"
@{b}@{u}Address@{uu}@{ub}

  The Address allows the viewing, editing, deleting, and adding of items.  Selecting an item allows its contents to be viewed in the right-hand side area.  Double-clicking of items opens up an edit window for that item.

  It is also possible to import and export CSV (comma seperated value) files from the Address book.
  The format each line in the CSV file follows is:

  @{i}"last name","first name","company","title","phone 1","phone 2","phone 3","phone 4","phone 5","address","city","state","zip","country","custom 1","custom 2","custom 3","custom 4"@{ui}

  · To export, just select all the required files, and select Export form the pull-down menus.  In the request, type in the file name for the CSV file to be saved.
  · To import CSV files, select Import from the pull-down menus, and select a CSV file for import.
@endnode

@node ToDo "To Do"
@{b}@{u}To Do@{uu}@{ub}

  The To Do allows the viewing, editing, deleting, and adding of items.  Double-clicking of items opens up an edit window for that item.  Clicking on a note icon will open up the note window.
@endnode

@node Date "Date"
@{b}@{u}Date@{uu}@{ub}

  The Datebook allows the viewing, editing, deleting, and adding of items.  Double-clicking of items opens up an edit window for that item.  Clicking on a note icon will open up the note window.

  NOTE: Currently not completed.
@endnode


