@node "FAQ" "Frequently Asked Questions"
@next "Author"
@prev "TipsAndTricks"

Q. How do I do easily do a complete backup of my Palm?
A. Select the menu item @{b}Backup@{ub} from under the menu @{b}Action@{ub}. Spitfire will
   automatically adjust the conduit actions and do a backup.

Q. How do I do easily do a complete restoration of my Palm?
A. Select the menu item @{b}Restore@{ub} from under the menu @{b}Action@{ub}. Spitfire will
   automatically adjust the conduit actions and restore your Palm.

Q. I do not like the user name that my Palm has set.  Is there a way to
   change it?
A. Choose the menu item @{b}Change User Name@{ub} from the menu @{b}Action@{ub}.

Q. Can I "virginize" my Palm with Spitfire?
A. Choose the menu item @{b}Change User Name@{ub} from the menu @{b}Action@{ub} and set the
   string gadget to be empty.

Q. Can I install applications files without doing an entire HotSync?
A. Use the menu item @{b}Install Files@{ub} from the menu @{b}Action@{ub}.

Q. How come hitting RETURN in some string gadgets (i.e. Address editing) causes the line to disappear?
A. The PalmOS, and some other OS (i.e. Windows) have the ability to expand their string gadgets
   into multi-line editing gadgets.  The Amiga (and MUI) cannot do this, thus in order to be able to
   support the PalmOS's ability a kludge was needed.  Hitting RETURN will not erase the line, but
   create a new line.  Use the cursor keys to navigate in the string gadget.  To move to the  next
   string gadget use the TAB key.


Please email me at <torchia@windsor.igs.net> if you have problems that cannot be solved or answered.

@endnode


