@{b}@{u}Version History@{uu}@{ub}

 * v0.4  - Initial release.
 * v0.5  - Corrected non-functional Abort button.  A double-click of the button
           should not work properly.
         - Corrected bug in username lister in which a cancelling of editing
           a user name brought up a requester.
         - Worked a bit more on the guide file.
   v0.6  - Complete overhaul of the GUI
   v0.7  - Update of Guide file
         - Correct datatype image loading problem.
         - Created install script
 * v0.8  - Still coding the conduits (memo pad and address book are partially
           completed)
         - Some internal changes to the code
         - Corrected several minor problems with Spitfire.guide
 * v0.9  - Corrected install script not copying main Spitfire file to correct
           destination directory
         - Fixed problem with Spitfire crashing when being started for the
           first time for a user and in demo mode.
 * v0.10 - Forgot to update the main archive with the last compiled version
           of Spitfire.  Two problems it had, which were fixed were 1) Demo
           requester appearing for registered users 2) subsequent openning
           of Address conduit would created wrong number of cycle gadgets in
           edit window.
   v0.11 - Minor changes and bug fixes to backup and restore routines.
         - Fixed problem of duplicate categories in edit fields of address and
           memo conduit applications
         - Began coding sync routines for memo pad.  Syncing of Memos functional
           but not syncing of Memo categories.
         - Major changes to workings of Memo conduit
         - Implemented usage of Nlist and NFloattext
   v0.12 - Correct bug in memo syncing.
         - Began implementing syncing of categories for memos (not active yet).
         - Several minor changes to Spitfire and memo conduit code.
   v0.13 - Added ability to change a Palm's user name id.
         - Fixed some problems in synchronizing of memos.
         - Fixed problem of certain requesters popping up at the wrong times.
   v0.14 - Sync log listview now becomes active at HotSync.
         - Disabled parts in conduits that are not fully completed for hotsyncing
         - To Do conduit now allows viewing of To Do items
         - Re-wrote many parts of the Address conduit
         - If there were zero items in Memos or Address then enforcer hits occured
   v0.15 - Fixed typo in window title bar of Address book.
         - Memo pad now respects private/secret attribute.
         - Memo editor now displays private flag setting.
         - If change made to the same memo on the Amiga and Palm, then the Amiga
           overwrites Palm memo at sync.
         - Removed "synchronize the files" for system conduit since option made no
           real sense for the conduit.
         - Implemented new log list updater for the main Spitfire program
           from the throttle process.  Should cure the graphci glitches reported
           by some.
         - Log listview now also using NList.
         - Address book will now display and sort by company name in listview if
           first and last name fields are blank for an entry.
 * v0.16 - Had a major HD crash in which I lost most of my HD (in fact, my HD is
           now dead, and I had to buy a new one).  Luckly I did have a recent backup
           of the source code for Spitfire on floppy.  I had to re-install and
           re-create my development environment though...
         - Changed demo expiration date to June 1, 1999.
         - Finished synchronizing of Addresses!
         - Entering notes greater than the Palm limit of 4000 characters would
           crash Spitfire.  This also could result in crashes with cut'n'paste
           feature of the textinput note editor.
         - Fixed illegal access of memory in Memo and Address which could cause
           unpredictable crashes.
   v0.17 - Fixed some more possible memory access bugs.
         - Conduits now properly dispose of their MUI gui elements.
         - Cleaned up some illegal memory accesses in Spitfire throttle process.
         - After editing of an Address item the viewed address is now correctly updated.
         - Enabled menu item "Conduit->To Do".  Forgot to do it last time.
         - Added Memo export, with multi-selection to memo conduit.  I was going to do
           this at a later time, but several people have been asking about it.
         - Added Memo importing of ASCII files.
         - Enhanced deleting of Memo items with support for multi-selection.
         - Fixed spelling mistake in "Database" word.
         - Modified code that adds items to log file listview.
         - Fixed bug in Install conduit's file requester.
         - Log listview was not jumping to the last line as it scrolled.
         - Added new image to About requester.  This requester is also created as needed
           now, so it will save some memory (How many times does someone actually open
           the About window?).  For unregistered users though, this means the
           window and image are created/disposed with each opening/closing.  Sorry...
         - Added ability to load external images for checkmarks, notes, alarms, and repeat
           events. These images are now used in the conduits.
         - Did I ever mention that all Spitfire images are loaded using Datatypes? ;-)
         - All string gadgets in Address edit window now support multiple line entries. Useing
           cursor keys to go up/down the buffer allows viewing of multiple lines at one
           line entry at a time.  Hitting return will create a new line (use cursor up to
           get to previous line).
         - Double-clicking on the Install conduit in the Conduit Action listview when
           the file count is zero will now bring up a file requester for adding files.
         - Datebook is somewhat funtional now.  It allows viewing of entries and notes.
           Still need to finish the edit window, synchronizing, and implement date
           exceptions for datebook events.
 * v0.18 - Updated install script to properly install required libraries and MUI
           custom classes.
         - Added Importing and Exporting of Address items in CSV (comma seperated values)
           format.
         - Added multiple selection for exporting and deleting in Address.
         - Made changes to Memo and Address menus, with addition of a select all and none items
         - Changed appearence of Export/Import status windows.
         - Rewrote system backup code to fix some problems and memory leaks (didn't anyone
           notice these problems besides myself?)
         - Opening and closing of conduits several times lead to major memory leaks.
 * v0.19 - The datebook wasn't cleaning up after itself!
         - Modified ToDo list column titles.
         - Added deletion and addition of todo items.
         - Added ability to synchronize todo items.
         - ToDo items should now be sorted by completion.
         - Double-clicking in Note column now allows editing of notes for the selected item.
         - Removed redundant Export and Import menus from Memo and Address.
         - Added Import/Export of Addresses from/to CManager.
         - Device name in Spitfire prefs was truncating devices which where longer than 15
           characters.  Max limit now at 25, which should handle all serial devices.
         - Fixed changing of username id so that pressing Cancel or not altering the user name
           will not cause a syncing.
         - Spitfire would not properly backup system files if user directory was empty or
           only conduit .pdb files exited.
         - Fixed problem of new memos added from Amiga not syncing with Palm.
         - Other minor fixes here and there.
   v0.20 - Restoring databases to a Palm was not working correctly. Hopefully it now works
           as it should.
         - Minor fixes in scanning for serial devices.
         - Probably some other stuff I don't remember
         - Began work on SpitfireNG... :-)
 * v0.21 - Fixed problem of imported items not being synced if they were not edited first.
         - Filter for install requester changed from *.(prc|pdb) to #?.(prc|pdb), since
           some systems do not have wildstar support activated.
         - Again fix a small problem in the scanning of serial devices on systems (sigh...)
 * v0.22 - Forgot to change the expiration date!  Opps...
 * v0.23 - Change expiration date for demo version to Dec. 31/99
         - Addition of NewIcon Images by Phil Vedovatti!
         - Items that were added from Spitfire for Memos, ToDo, and Address Book were not
           being properly synced.
         - Added latest textinput classes to archive.
         - Update of install script for installing new images.
 * v0.24 - Address exports to CManager were having email entries clipped to 19 characters and
           city entries would have comma inserted when no state/province was available
         - Last category show now remembered by Memo, ToDo, and Address book.
         - Fixed typos in Bubble help of Address book.
         - Close gadgets added to Note editors.
         - Removed some debugging info that was being output to CON:
         - Localization of Spitfire!
   v0.25 - Addition of svenska catalog file
         - Update of installation script
         - Fixed bug in wrong locale text for certain items.
   v0.26 - Default language of "english" was not set for locale.library, resulting in Spitfire
           searching for an english spitfire.catalog.
         - Fixed non-working localization of installer script text.
         - Updated Textinput classes and associated libraries.
 * v0.27 - Installer script had a misplaced comment character, resulting in its failure on
           execution.
         - Changed the Address Book's address field to display multiple lines (All fields in the
           edit window are multiple lines, you just see one line at a time.  Wish MUI could do
           an auto-expand of string gadgets without having to close the window and re-create the
           display).
         - Fixed wrong locale text in "okay" button of the Address book's Rename Custom field
           window.
         - Add simple name/company search feature to Address book.
 * v0.28 - Change some of the text in the German catalog as suggested by Richard Körber and Ingo
           Heinichke
         - Updated date.library to latest release
         - CSV export/import from Address book now require fields to be enclosed in quotes (")
         - Did some minor changes in the code.
         - Some changes to guide file.
 * v0.29 - date.library v33.310 caused date entries to be miss-sorted in the datebook.
         - ToDo entries are now sorted by priority, then by date.
         - Memos can now be exported to a single file or multiple files.
         - Clicking on the image buttons text in the toolbar now opens the application.
         - Spitfire sync subtask was illegally accessing the main Spitfire GUI, causing enforcer
           hits and lockups after several syncs.
 * v0.30 - Changed manner in which each conduit application saves its last used category.
           IMPORTANT! = open each conduit application, choose a category, and close it to set the
           new prefs file!
         - Found some more illegal accesses from the subtask towards the main MUI gui.
         - Slight code change in file requester for Installer of Palm databases.
         - Creating a new Address entry with a note would result in a blank entry being created
           with the note, instead of the intended created entry.
 * v0.31 - Hopefully squashed the bugs/enforcer hits that many reported with the last release,
           which was causing many crashes...
         - Minor code changes in the throttle subtask
         - New menu item "Web Site" added.  You can now visit the Spitfire home page (still under
           construction) if you have openurl.library installed.
 * v0.32 - ToDo sync routines were not releasing all its memory at its completion
         - Install now recognizes all PalmOS installable file extensions (.prc, .pdb, .pdq, .pnc,
           and .scp)
         - Fixed other memory leaks in the desktop applications and sync routines.
         - Fixed bug with converting Palm filenames to Amiga filenames
         - Fixed bugs with Spitfire attempting to open MUI interface when GUI was not properly
           created by MUI.
         - Log text can now be highlighted and copied to clipboard (Amiga-X)
         - Spitfire was not disposing of entire MUI interface properly.
         - Updated textinput classes and vapor_toolkit.library
 * v0.33 - Bumped expiration date on unregistered copies of Spitfire.
         - .pqa were not being recognized by install. Fixed.


 (an asterisks (*) indicates an Aminet Release)

@endnode

@node "Future" "Future"
@next "Main"
@prev "History"
Write to me and tell me what would be cool to add to Spitfire!

Things that are currently planned:

 · Import/Export of To Do items in CSV format.
 · Full synchronizing of all standard Palm conduits.
 · Drag'n'drop of .prc/.pdb files onto Spitfire for syncing.
 · Importing files by drag'n'droping into conduits.
 · Modified XEN, XHelvetica, Times, and Helvetica fonts that incorporate
   the missing glyphs that the Palm supports.
 · Better documentation (I hate doing this kind of stuff...)

Additional suggestions by users:

 · Email conduit - I would like to do one, but my PalmPilot Personal does not have an
   email applications, thus there is no way for me to develope one. :-(
 · Conversion of text files into Doc format.
 · Full ARexx port and access to all of Spitfire's features.
 · Saving of log files.

@endnode

